description: Generates a list of all model versions for a given model, including the model version, model version ARN, and status. To list a subset of versions, use the MaxModelVersion and MinModelVersion fields.

parameters.name: ModelName
parameters.description: Then name of the machine learning model for which the model versions are to be listed.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If the total number of results exceeds the limit that the response can display, the response returns an opaque pagination token indicating where to continue the listing of machine learning model versions. Use this token in the NextToken field in the request to list the next page of results.

nested_items.name: ModelVersionSummaries
nested_items.description: Provides information on the specified model version, including the created time, model and dataset ARNs, and status.

nested_items.name: ModelName
nested_items.description: The name of the model that this model version is a version of.

nested_items.name: ModelArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the model that this model version is a version of.

nested_items.name: ModelVersionArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the model version.

nested_items.name: CreatedAt
nested_items.description: The time when this model version was created.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The current status of the model version.

nested_items.name: SourceType
nested_items.description: Indicates how this model version was generated.

nested_items.name: ModelQuality
nested_items.description: Provides a quality assessment for a model that uses labels. If Lookout for Equipment determines that the model quality is poor based on training metrics, the value is POOR_QUALITY_DETECTED. Otherwise, the value is QUALITY_THRESHOLD_MET.
